n 10:10 which she founded in the UK in September 2009, and which is now active in more than 50 countries. On International Women's Day, 8 March 2011, she was named as one of The Guardian newspaper's \"Top 100 Women\", in a list which included Aung San Suu Kyi, Gareth Peirce, Doris Lessing, Arundhati Roy and Oprah Winfrey. Her father is the television producer Peter Armstrong.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-09-05T19:40:21.822413+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 5809, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Franny_Armstrong"}], "uuid": "230c6604-83b8-473c-8ab5-cf9b55f99913", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "18967", "external_references": [{"id": 51209, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q435814"}, {"id": 54414, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "227176320"}, {"id": 54415, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "no99067354"}, {"id": 54416, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-no99067354"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-05T19:40:28.547151+10:00"}, {"id": 78867, "name": "Dick Beilby", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 3083117, "title": "The Water planet", "work_id": 91561, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3083124, "title": "Amazing H2o", "work_id": 91562, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3083132, "title": "Floating, sinking, swimming", "work_id": 91572, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3083141, "title": "Taps and toilets", "work_id": 91573, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3083150, "title": "Waterworks", "work_id": 115579, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2190187, "title": "Pathways to Australian science: 2 thinking scientifically about crime", "work_id": 88380, "role": "producer/director", "role_id": 31, "is_primary"